@freyhk @tripperhead Guess what, the CHP has a different take in its pdf version regarding negative RAT results (see #6)🤣
https://t.co/dgM1oJK2zG
@tripperhead What about those Recived sms positive case and they   Rapid test again at home. it’s showing negative?
@tripperhead I think I would reverse the phrasing if I were the CHP. If you test positive, you likely *are* infected (i.e. false positives are rare).
@tripperhead The other thing is the “test frequently”. Do they have any idea how much these tests cost retail?
@tripperhead 'likely not infected' does imply some degrees of probabilistic uncertainties.
@freyhk @tripperhead I think 'likely' in 'likely infected' is the key word here
@stripeygoodness @freyhk @maxxedcom @tripperhead Where can we find effectiveness of the various RAT tests available
@freyhk @maxxedcom @tripperhead Which I don’t think under the current environment anybody is right now…
